-- Ukraine Winter Grain Plantings Advance 3.8% This Year
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2011-12-20T14:23:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/ukraine-winter-grain-plantings-rise-3-8-this-year-agency-says.html
Farmers in Ukraine planted 8.39
million hectares (20.7 million acres) of land with winter grains
such as wheat, barley and rye so far this year, up 3.8 percent
from 2010, according to the country’s statistics agency.  The area planted with winter wheat increased 2.4 percent to
6.71 million hectares, while winter barley sowing climbed 10
percent to 1.37 million hectares,the Kiev-based office said in a
 statement  on its website today. Winter rapeseed has been planted
on 961,600 hectares, 11 percent less than a year earlier,
according to the statement.  About 27 percent of winter grains, or 1.69 million
hectares, were in good condition as of Dec. 15, according to the
 Agriculture Ministry ’s data. Satisfactory winter grains were
found on 39 percent of the area and weak plants on 34 percent.  Winter grains failed to emerge on 1.9 million hectares, the
ministry said. Winter rapeseed sprouted on 79 percent of areas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
